assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Warba Capital Holding Company K.S.C.P. engages in investment, and manufacturing and trading activities in Kuwait and internationally. The company invests in group funds in various sectors, including industrial, utilities, services, and other related sectors. It also manufactures cement blocks; and invests in and develops real estate projects. In addition, the company owns shares and equities of Kuwait and foreign shareholdings, as well as limited liability companies or participates in the association of these companies. Further, it engages in lending activities for companies, as well as owns rights of industrial property such as patents, industrial trademarks, industrial fees, or other rights to lease them to other companies. The company was formerly known as Boubyan International Industries Holding Company K.S.C.P. and changed its name to Warba Capital Holding Company K.S.C.P. in January 2019. The company was founded in 2004 and is based in Sharq, Kuwait. Warba Capital Holding Company K.S.C.P. is a subsidiary of Boubyan Petrochemical Company K.S.C.P.
